.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [command_file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C.
It reads commands from standard input or from a file and executes them,
mimicking basic behavior of the standard /bin/sh shell.

The shell supports:
.IP \[bu] 2
Execution of commands in both interactive and non-interactive modes.
.IP \[bu] 2
Handling of the PATH environment variable to locate executables.
.IP \[bu] 2
Built-in commands such as
.BR exit
and
.BR env .
.IP \[bu] 2
Error handling and proper process management using
.BR fork (2)
and
.BR execve (2) .

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run in interactive mode:
.EX
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
($) exit
.EE
.TP
Run in non-interactive mode:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.EE

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Almansour Khaled Shaden and Teammate Name.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2)

